  "description": "A soft hand in [blackjack](../index.md) is a hand that contains an ace counted as 11 without causing a [bust](./bust.md) [@thorp1966]. For example, ace-six is a soft 17. If the player takes another card and would otherwise go over 21, the ace can convert from 11 to 1 and the hand becomes hard instead of busting.",
  "name": "soft hand",
